                    <h3>About the Idea</h3>
                    <p class="fst-italic" style="font-size:18px">
                        Health insurance is among the most complicated and costly products that consumers buy. Lacking health insurance realted knowledge and skills-or health literacy-puts people at risk of choosing an insurance product that could fail to provide needed benefits or protect them financially.
                    </p>

                    <ul style="font-weight:bold">
                        <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>Our product aims to help the insurance companies to identify and gather the information related to socio-economic profiles of people in both rural and urban areas and help categorizing them according to their insurance needs while correlating to their various life and general insurance paramaters.</li>
                        <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>Our proposed solution is divided into 3 main parts -<br />  1)Data Collection:Regional analysis pertaining to an area,<br /> 2)Data Extraction: The data collected is passed through a set of functions/action events to categorize it into 2 different groups & <br />3)Action: With the help of above extracted data and data groups, it will aid the insurance companies to identify such target groups/customers and help them bridge a gap by taking subsequent actions (such as Insurance awarness drives or determining Real-time premium)</li>
                        <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>This idea will result in providing 2 solutions -<br />1)Finding the Focus Group &; <br />2)Determining the Real Time Premium </li>
                        <li><i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i>Insurance literacy and Real-time premiums will not only help to balance the existing risk covers with better insurance products and services but also make a difference in expanding insurability by improving offers to individuals who would otherwise have been declined or substandard while better matching risk to premiums. </li>
                       
                    </ul>
                    <p class="fst-italic" style="font-size:18px">
                      
                        Thus, assessing health insurance literacy can help identify what health insurance aspects pose the greatest problems for customers, which groups need more assistance to enroll and use benefits, and what topics and skills consumer-counselling efforts should focus on.
                    </p>
